9 AS INTRODUCED
10 An Act relating to the Council on Law Enforcement
Education and Training; amending 70 O.S. 2021,
11 Section 3311, as last amended by Section 1, Chapter
65, O.S.L. 2024 (70 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 3311),
12 which relates to the creation of the Council on Law
Enforcement Education and Training; modifying
13 qualifications of the Executive Director; and
providing an effective date.
14
15
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 3311, as
19 last amended by Section 1, Chapter 65, O.S.L. 2024 (70 O.S. Supp.
20 2025, Section 3311), is amended to read as follows:
21 Section 3311. A. There is hereby created a Council on Law
22 Enforcement Education and Training which shall be, and is hereby
23 declared to be, a governmental law enforcement agency of the State
24 of Oklahoma, body politic and corporate, with powers of government
HB3055 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 and with the authority to exercise the rights, privileges and
2 functions necessary to ensure the professional training and
3 continuing education of law enforcement officers in this state.
4 These rights, privileges and functions include, but are not limited
5 to, those specified in Sections 3311 through 3311.15 of this title
6 and in the Oklahoma Security Guard and Private Investigator Act and
7 the Bail Enforcement and Licensing Act. The Council shall be
8 authorized to require agency employees and the employees of agency
9 contractors in positions to have access to Oklahoma Peace Officer
10 records, Oklahoma Security Guard and Private Investigator records,
11 Bail Enforcement and Licensing Act records, to be subject to a
12 criminal history search by the Oklahoma State Bureau of
13 Investigation, as well as be fingerprinted for submission of the
14 fingerprints through the Oklahoma State Bureau of Investigation to
15 the Federal Bureau of Investigation for a national criminal history
16 check. The Council shall be the recipient of the results of the
17 record check. In accordance with Section 150.9 of Title 74 of the
18 Oklahoma Statutes, this includes a national criminal record with a
19 finger print analysis. The Council shall be composed of thirteen
20 (13) members as follows:
21 1. The Commissioner of the Department of Public Safety, or
22 designee;
23 2. The Director of the Oklahoma State Bureau of Narcotics and
24 Dangerous Drugs Control, or designee;
